#####GW-BSE Calculation is 4 step calculation-scf, optics, GW, BSE
The common files for all calculation is KPOINTS, POSCAR, POTCAR
First step is scf
The WAVECAR file from scf calculation needs to be given to the optics calculation.
Second step is optics calculation
From the result files, the WAVECAR and WAVEDER files needs to be taken for GW calculation
Third step is GW Calculation
From the result files, all the wavecar and waveder files needs to be taken for BSE Calculation
This provide optical properties with excitonic effect
To get optical properties without excitonic effect, the GW-RPA Calculation needs to be done, after the third step.
